<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6DFFE64EFFFB8EFEACFAEB" blockId="23.[151,1437,1074,1531]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<materialsCitation id="3B7BB7102F6DFFE64EFFFB8EFE02FB77" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1503410417" collectionCode="MPEG" country="Brazil" county="Vitt" location="Avila-Pires" municipality="Balbina" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" specimenCode="MPEG 15313" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64EFFFB8EFE49FBE7" bold="true" box="[151,406,1074,1099]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Two specimens (
<specimenCode id="DBB515362F6DFFE64C1BFB8FFCC7FBE7" box="[627,792,1074,1099]" collectionCode="MPEG" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<collectionCode id="ED0225882F6DFFE64C1BFB8FFD1CFBE7" box="[627,707,1075,1099]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">MPEG</collectionCode>
15313
</specimenCode>
and 15815) mentioned by 
<location id="8ECCEB962F6DFFE64A1AFB8EFB2DFBE7" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BA0C5B2F6DFFE64EFFFC50FC33FA57:8ECCEB962F6DFFE64A1AFB8EFB2DFBE7" box="[1138,1266,1074,1099]" country="Brazil" county="Vitt" municipality="Balbina" name="Avila-Pires" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" stateProvince="Amazonas">Ávila-Pires</location>
(1995) under ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64EC8FBEBFE0AFBC2" box="[160,469,1110,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Leposoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64EC8FBEBFECBFBC2" box="[160,276,1111,1134]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Leposoma</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F56FBEBFE0AFBC2" box="[318,469,1111,1134]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, and those from 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC827372F6DFFE64CF4FBEAFD2CFBC3" box="[668,755,1110,1135]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Balbina</collectingMunicipality>
hydroelectric dam reservoir, 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64A55FBEBFB69FBC3" box="[1085,1206,1111,1135]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64AA9FBEAFAD7FBC3" box="[1217,1288,1110,1135]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, identified in that paper as 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64F42FBC0FE67FB3F" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[298,440,1148,1171]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guianense">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F42FBC0FE67FB3F" box="[298,440,1148,1171]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. guianense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, represent this group. 
<collectingCounty id="62CDC5C12F6DFFE64CD8FBC6FD05FB3F" box="[688,730,1146,1171]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Vitt</collectingCounty>
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64C89FBC0FCC6FB3F" box="[737,793,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
(2008) present characteristics that distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64B77FBC6FA43FB3F" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[1311,1436,1146,1171]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64B77FBC6FA43FB3F" box="[1311,1436,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. from 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64F6AFB22FDFFFB1A" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[258,544,1182,1207]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F6AFB22FDFFFB1A" box="[258,544,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occur in sympatry. 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64D0AFB22FC00FB1B" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[866,991,1182,1207]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64D0AFB22FC00FB1B" box="[866,991,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. is also partially sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64BEDFB23FED6FB77" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guianense">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64BEDFB23FED6FB77" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. guianense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
close to the 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64FC2FB7FFE02FB77" box="[426,477,1219,1243]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Pará</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
– 
<materialsCitation id="3B7BB7102F6DFFE64F83FB7FFEACFAEB" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1503410421" country="Brazil" location="Amazonas" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas">
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64F83FB7FFDBFFB77" box="[491,608,1219,1243]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
state border. Pellegrino 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64DECFB78FC1DFB77" box="[900,962,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
(2011) recovered, in a molecular study, 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64EFFFB5AFECBFB53" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,276,1254,1279]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64EFFFB5AFECBFB53" box="[151,276,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (which they called 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64C4FFB5BFCF4FB53" box="[551,811,1254,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Leposoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osvaldoi">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64C4FFB5BFD45FB52" box="[551,666,1255,1278]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Leposoma</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64CA4FB5AFCF4FB53" box="[716,811,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">osvaldoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64A58FB5BFB70FB53" box="[1072,1199,1254,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Leposoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osvaldoi">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64A58FB5BFB70FB53" box="[1072,1199,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. osvaldoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, only one specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64F4EFAB6FE7CFA8F" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[294,419,1290,1315]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64F4EFAB6FE7CFA8F" box="[294,419,1290,1315]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. was included in the analysis and additional studies are necessary to establish how they relate to each other.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6DFFE64EAFFAEEFC33FA57" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6DFFE64EAFFAEEFC33FA57" blockId="23.[151,1437,1074,1531]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64EAFFAEEFE21FAC7" bold="true" box="[199,510,1362,1387]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64C64FAEEFD56FAC7" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[524,649,1362,1387]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64C64FAEEFD56FAC7" box="[524,649,1362,1387]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. is endemic to northern Brazilian 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64A3EFAEEFB16FAC7" box="[1110,1225,1362,1387]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="23" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
(restricted to the southern part of the 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6DFFE64F1FFACAFE17FA23" box="[375,456,1398,1423]" name="Guyana" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Guiana</collectingCountry>
region), with its distribution delimited by the Paru do Oeste, Amazon, and Negro rivers (
<figureCitation id="1328A1C82F6DFFE64EF7FA26FF29FA1F" box="[159,246,1434,1459]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1126,1148]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,203,1100]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1105]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 15. Distribution of examined material of Loxopholis sp., Neusticurus rudis, and Potamites ecpleopus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581990/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). It is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64C1DFA27FD78FA1F" box="[629,679,1435,1459]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Pará</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6DFFE64C8CFA27FC81FA1F" box="[740,862,1435,1459]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64D04FA26FC36FA1F" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[876,1001,1434,1459]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64D04FA26FC36FA1F" box="[876,1001,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary terra firme and flooded (varzea) forests, where it is found among leaf litter and fallen palm leaves (Martins 1991b—identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6DFFE64FE1FA58FDC7FA57" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[393,536,1508,1531]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guianense">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64FE1FA58FDC7FA57" box="[393,536,1508,1531]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. guianense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Vitt 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64C30FA58FD4EFA57" box="[600,657,1506,1531]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2008; Ávila-Pires 
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6DFFE64D0CFA58FC42FA57" box="[868,925,1506,1531]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2010).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
